yz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/12/02 12:49:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=413.topic&index=41>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> RE: Root/Nuke</span><hr size=1> Aye, I mem Tishans and Markars clash. I start with Markars and if (and i rarely get resisted) it gets resisted i have Tishan ready to go. Once stunned (which btw Markars has a dd stunn of 200+), i click my flux staff snare and nuke away. If root breaks SO WHAT its snared why would i waste mana to nuke re root, nuke re root,  nuke re root,  nuke re rooting it again? I just run a little turn around nuke, run a little turn around nuke. Rinse and repeat. Similar concepts as quading but if the mob is a under coned drk blue I use this tactic for singles. <br>
<br>
Run Down<br>
Stunn - Flux - Snare - Nuke - Nuke - Nuke.<br>
Markars - Flux - Atols - Drought - Drought - Drought.<br>
<br>
<br>
I dont use Ice comet no more i get more DD out of my drought spells casting them twice ( 3 sec cast time for drought; totalling 6 secs) than casting 1 Ice comet, cast time 6 secs.<br>
<br>
<br>
Keuamen B'Hunter<br>
51st Channeler in Xegony<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ucereswhirlwind.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ceres Whirlwind</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/13/02 7:41:01 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=413.topic&index=42>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: RE: Root/Nuke</span><hr size=1> I usually use root/nuke whenever I am dealing with only one or two mobs. I put up a skin and start off by rooting the mob. If I am lucky I can kill a blue with 3 nukes and the root doesnt break. If the root breaks, my skin will keep me in one piece while I reroot. Even in a pinch I am able to channel through a root or a gate. So if that skin breaks rerooting is no problem. Root/nuke is one of the best methods for singles. Snare costs more mana and it takes more time and space to kite that mob around. Sometimes I do root and snare, so if root breaks I can reroot before it reaches me.<br>
In dungeons I don't bother to move father away then out of melee range before I start nuking again. Space is limited there anyway.<br>
<br>
Ceres Whirlwind<br>
Lvl 48 Wizard<br>
Vazaelle <p><IMG SRC="http://unet.univie.ac.at/~a9602399/misc/Sig2.jpg" BORDER="0"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=sageaspiitfiire>Sagea Spiitfiire</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/16/02 1:36:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=413.topic&index=43>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Root/Nuke : Fact or fantasy?</span><hr size=1> I thrived on root &amp; nuke until I could scribe bonds of force. I was determined not to group much until I had my defense up over 100 and root and nuke will help you make that happen, for sure. Won lots of fights with less than a bub of health...lost a few too.<br>
<br>
While I see the sense in leading with your highest nuke, one thing I learned for pulling to a safe spot was to lead with tishan's clash. I used this a lot in the hills between Fv and the Mill in LIO. What it does, is it gives you a headstart. The stun effect lets you hightail your fanny to your safe pull spot and it not resisted, you should have time to turn around and land a root on most mobs as they are incoming. If it's safe to fight where you find the mob, sure, lead with the high nuke. If it's suicide from sure adds where you pull from, try this technique.<br>
<br>
Best luck,<br>
<br>
<br>
Sagea Spiitfiire<br>
Wizard of 35 Seasons<br>
Ayonae Ro Server <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uaazraaell.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aazraaell</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/22/02 9:44:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=413.topic&index=44>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Root/Nuke : Fact or fantasy?</span><hr size=1>  Dinged 60 soloin in Seb with root/nuke. Really is dangerous business though. Recommend sow potions at that level if your detemined to keep at it. Also, skin yourself. The mob is gonna break root, it will beat your head in and you gotta take the hits and recast root with him beatin on ya. All part of the process. If you hps, spell protection, and channeling skill are not high enough at that level to be able to take a poundin till a root sticks, root/nuke is not a viable solo option at that level. <br>
<br>
    Honestly, Id stick to groupin till ya get bonds of force at least. Then you can kite, which is somewhat safer, or if you want to do root/nuke (maybe ya like soloin in cramped dungeons) can throw a snare on first and give yourself ahead start on rerooting the mob when it breaks initial root. Used to root/nuke solo in lower guk like that in my 30s. <br>
<br>
   As far as enstill/ para earth line....a comment was made that how often it breaks is dumb luck for all roots. In my experience that line (parking line) was practically a guarnteed break on first nuke. I truly dont believe they are effective at all as root/nuke roots. They are definitely for splittin/ghetto mezzin.  Longer max duration if left untouched. But the shorter max duration root line i believe has a greater chance of holdin through a nuke.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showMessageRange?topicID=413.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a><a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showMessageRange?topicID=413.topic&start=21&stop=40>2</a> <b>3</b>  </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showPrevMessage?topicID=413.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showNextMessage?topicID=413.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=413.topic&index=44><img src=http://www.graffe.com/messageboard/add_reply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.emailToFriend?topicID=413.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.threadControl?topicID=413.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=413.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to rece